@node Overview
@chapter Overview
@cindex overview

The OptionMatrix programs are financial derivative calculators
distributed by @url{http://@value{WEBSITE}}.
These calculators are real-time multi-model option chain pricers with
analytics and interactive controls. @command{optionmatrix} is the GTK+ graphical user interface version and @command{optionmatrix_console} is the Curses version (Unix/Linux console, DOS).

Both programs feature: greeks, decimal date to real-date translations, real-date to decimal date translations, real-time time bleeding, configurable option expiration date engines, calendars, strike control systems, tickers and over 170 option models. @command{optionmatrix} also supports: spreads, bonds, term structures, cash flow editing, source code viewing and text exporting.

